\newlabel{fig:plot5}{{5}{10}{Gradient norm $\|\nabla L\|$ vs iteration on a log scale. The perfectly straight line confirms \textbf {linear convergence} with a constant rate. GD and Newton are indistinguishable, as expected for a quadratic loss with constant Hessian}{figure.caption.9}{}}
